    "question_en": "Why doesn't God answer my prayers?",
    "short_answer_zh": "上帝总是回应祷告，但不总是按照我们期望的方式。祂的回应可能是「是」「不」或「等候」——每一种回应都出于祂完美的智慧和爱。",
    "short_answer_en": "God always responds to prayer, but not always in the way we expect. His answer may be 'yes,' 'no,' or 'wait' — each from His perfect wisdom and love.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "首先，上帝确实回应了每一个祷告——只是不一定是我们期望的回应方式。一个好父亲不会答应孩子的每一个要求，因为有些要求对孩子并不好。上帝有时候说「不」或「还没到时候」，正是因为祂知道什么对我们真正有益。\n\n其次，圣经也提到了几个可能妨碍祷告的因素：未悔改的罪（赛59:2）、错误的动机（雅4:3）、对他人的不饶恕（可11:25）、不信（雅1:6-7）。这些不是说上帝记仇或斤斤计较，而是说罪会阻碍我们与上帝的沟通。\n\n最终，我们必须学习信靠上帝的智慧超过我们自己的理解。保罗三次求上帝除去他身上的「刺」，但上帝说：「我的恩典够你用的」（林后12:9）。有时候我们后来才明白，上帝没有给我们想要的，是因为祂给了我们更好的。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "First, God does respond to every prayer — just not always as we expect. A good father doesn't grant every request because some aren't good for the child. God sometimes says 'no' or 'not yet' precisely because He knows what's truly beneficial.\n\nSecond, Scripture mentions factors that may hinder prayer: unrepented sin (Isa 59:2), wrong motives (James 4:3), unforgiveness toward others (Mark 11:25), and unbelief (James 1:6-7). This doesn't mean God holds grudges but that sin disrupts our communication with Him.\n\nUltimately, we must learn to trust God's wisdom above our own understanding. Paul asked three times for God to remove his 'thorn,' but God said: 'My grace is sufficient for you' (2 Cor 12:9). Sometimes we later realize God didn't give us what we wanted because He gave us something better.",
