    "id": "q063",
    "category": "authority_of_scripture",
    "question_zh": "怎么证明圣经是上帝的话，而不只是人写的书？",
    "question_en": "How can you prove the Bible is God's Word and not just a human book?",
    "short_answer_zh": "圣经的预言应验、科学前瞻、内部一致性、生命改变力，以及历经两千年批判仍屹立不倒的事实，都证明它超越了人的智慧。",
    "short_answer_en": "Fulfilled prophecy, scientific foresight, internal consistency, life-transforming power, and surviving 2,000 years of criticism all prove the Bible transcends human wisdom.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "圣经与其他一切书籍有根本的不同：\n\n1.【独特的来源】圣经是唯一一本以造物主第一人称向人类说话的书。66卷书，约40位作者，跨越1500年，却从头到尾信息一致。这就像一部交响乐——不同乐手、不同时代，却有一位总指挥。\n\n2.【预言的应验】以色列亡国超过一千年后竟然在1948年复国——这在圣经中早已预言。圣经还预言了世界局势、基督的降生地点和方式等等，全部精确应验。\n\n3.【科学的前瞻】在人类还以为地球是平的时候，以赛亚书40:22已经说「神坐在地球大圈之上」；约伯记26:7说「将大地悬在虚空」。这些知识远超当时的科学水平。\n\n4.【生命改变的能力】历史上无数人因圣经的话从罪中得释放、从绝望中找到盼望。没有第二本书有这样的力量。\n\n5.【不可摧毁】历代以来多少人试图消灭或推翻圣经，全部失败。它至今仍是全球最畅销的书，已被翻译成超过两千种语言。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "The Bible is fundamentally different from all other books:\n\n1. **Unique origin**: It's the only book where the Creator speaks in first person to humanity. 66 books, ~40 authors, spanning 1,500 years, yet internally consistent. Like a symphony — different musicians, different eras, but one conductor.\n\n2. **Fulfilled prophecy**: Israel was restored as a nation in 1948 after over 1,000 years of exile — prophesied in Scripture long beforehand. The Bible also predicted world events, Christ's birthplace and manner of death, all precisely fulfilled.\n\n3. **Scientific foresight**: When people still thought Earth was flat, Isaiah 40:22 already said God 'sits above the circle of the earth'; Job 26:7 says He 'hangs the earth on nothing.' This knowledge far exceeded the science of those times.\n\n4. **Life-transforming power**: Throughout history, countless people have been freed from sin and found hope through Scripture. No other book has this power.\n\n5. **Indestructible**: Throughout the ages, many have tried to eliminate or refute the Bible — all have failed. It remains the world's bestselling book, translated into over 2,000 languages.",
