    "category": "existence_of_god",
    "question_zh": "上帝为什么要创造宇宙和人类？",
    "question_en": "Why did God create the universe and humanity?",
    "short_answer_zh": "上帝创造宇宙是为了彰显祂的荣耀，创造人类是出于爱——祂渴望与我们建立亲密的关系，分享祂的美善。",
    "short_answer_en": "God created the universe to display His glory and humanity out of love — He desires intimate relationship with us, sharing His goodness.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "诗篇19:1说「诸天述说神的荣耀，穹苍传扬祂的手段。」整个宇宙就像一幅巨大的画作，展示画家的才华和荣美。从星系的壮丽到细胞的精密，都在诉说造物主的全能和智慧。\n\n但上帝创造人不只是为了展示能力。正如父母在孩子出生前就开始为他预备房间、衣物、食物——这一切都出于爱。上帝为人类预备了适宜居住的地球，阳光、水、空气、食物，一切所需，然后将人安置其中。这说明上帝的大爱。\n\n约翰福音3:16说「上帝爱世人，甚至将祂的独生子赐给他们。」创造的终极目的不是让人成为被动的观众，而是让人回应上帝的爱，与祂建立真实的关系。\n\n用一句话概括：天是为着地，地是为着人，人是为着上帝。当我们认识上帝、荣耀上帝并以祂为乐时，我们就活出了被造的目的。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "Psalm 19:1 says 'The heavens declare the glory of God; the skies proclaim the work of his hands.' The entire universe is like a vast painting displaying the artist's skill and beauty. From the majesty of galaxies to the precision of cells, all speak of the Creator's power and wisdom.\n\nBut God didn't create humans merely to display power. Just as parents prepare a room, clothes, and food before their child is born — all out of love — God prepared Earth with sunlight, water, air, and food, everything needed, then placed humans within it. This reveals God's great love.\n\nJohn 3:16 says 'God so loved the world that he gave his only Son.' Creation's ultimate purpose isn't for humans to be passive spectators but to respond to God's love and enter a real relationship with Him.\n\nIn one sentence: heaven exists for earth, earth for humanity, humanity for God. When we know God, glorify Him, and delight in Him, we fulfill the purpose of our creation.",
