    "id": "q076",
    "category": "holy_spirit",
    "question_zh": "圣灵是谁？是一种力量还是位格？",
    "question_en": "Who is the Holy Spirit — a force or a person?",
    "short_answer_zh": "圣灵不是一种无形的力量或能量，而是三一上帝的第三位格——祂有意志、情感、智慧，是真正的神。",
    "short_answer_en": "The Holy Spirit is not an impersonal force or energy, but the third person of the Trinity — He has will, emotions, and intellect, and is truly God.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "许多人误以为圣灵只是一种神秘的能量或影响力，但圣经清楚表明圣灵是一个有位格的存在。\n\n1.【圣灵是位格】圣灵有智慧——祂鉴察万事（林前2:10）；有意志——祂随己意分给各人恩赐（林前12:11）；有情感——祂会担忧（弗4:30）。一股力量不会担忧，只有位格才会。耶稣称圣灵为「保惠师」（约14:16），用的是人称代词「祂」。\n\n2.【圣灵是神】彼得对欺哄圣灵的亚拿尼亚说「你不是欺哄人，是欺哄神了」（徒5:3-4），直接等同圣灵与神。圣灵无所不在（诗139:7）、无所不知（林前2:10-11）、参与创造（创1:2），这些都是神独有的属性。\n\n3.【圣灵与三一】在大使命中，耶稣吩咐奉父、子、圣灵的名施洗（太28:19），将三者并列。圣灵不是次等的神，而是与父和子同等、同荣、同永恒的一位神。\n\n理解圣灵的位格性至关重要——因为这意味着我们与圣灵的关系不是使用一种工具，而是与一位活着的神交通。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "Many people mistakenly think the Holy Spirit is merely a mysterious energy or influence, but Scripture clearly shows the Spirit is a personal being.\n\n1. **The Spirit is a person**: He has intellect — He searches all things (1 Cor 2:10); will — He distributes gifts as He determines (1 Cor 12:11); emotions — He can be grieved (Eph 4:30). A force cannot grieve; only a person can. Jesus called the Spirit the 'Helper' (John 14:16), using personal pronouns.\n\n2. **The Spirit is God**: Peter told Ananias, who lied to the Holy Spirit, 'You have not lied to man but to God' (Acts 5:3-4), directly equating the Spirit with God. The Spirit is omnipresent (Ps 139:7), omniscient (1 Cor 2:10-11), and participated in creation (Gen 1:2) — all attributes unique to God.\n\n3. **The Spirit and the Trinity**: In the Great Commission, Jesus commanded baptism in the name of the Father, Son, and Holy Spirit (Matt 28:19), placing all three together. The Spirit is not a lesser deity but co-equal, co-glorious, and co-eternal with the Father and Son.\n\nUnderstanding the Spirit's personhood is crucial — it means our relationship with Him is not using a tool, but communing with the living God.",
