    "id": "q079",
    "category": "holy_spirit",
    "question_zh": "什么是被圣灵充满？",
    "question_en": "What does it mean to be filled with the Holy Spirit?",
    "short_answer_zh": "被圣灵充满不是获得更多圣灵，而是让圣灵更多地掌管你的生命——顺服圣灵的引导，让祂的能力在你生命中自由运行。",
    "short_answer_en": "Being filled with the Spirit isn't receiving more of the Spirit, but letting the Spirit have more of you — submitting to His guidance and letting His power work freely in your life.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "被圣灵充满是基督徒生命中一个重要的概念，但常被误解。\n\n1.【内住与充满的区别】每个信徒在重生时就领受了圣灵的内住（罗8:9），这是一次性的、永久的。但圣灵充满是一个持续的经历——保罗命令说「要被圣灵充满」（弗5:18），用的是现在时态，表示这是一个持续不断的过程。\n\n2.【充满的意思】被圣灵充满不是一种神秘的狂喜体验，而是指圣灵完全掌管一个人的思想、意志和情感。就像醉酒的人被酒控制一样（保罗在弗5:18正是用这个对比），被圣灵充满的人是被圣灵的影响力所支配。\n\n3.【充满的表现】被圣灵充满的人会有几个标志：口里赞美神（弗5:19）、凡事感恩（弗5:20）、彼此顺服（弗5:21）、结出圣灵的果子（加5:22-23）、有胆量传讲真理（徒4:31）。\n\n4.【如何被充满】被圣灵充满不是靠追求某种特殊体验，而是通过认罪悔改、在神的话语中扎根、恒切祷告、在信心中顺服。当我们除去生命中的障碍物，圣灵就自然地充满我们。\n\n重要的是：圣灵充满不是少数属灵精英的特权，而是每位信徒的正常状态和责任。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "Being filled with the Spirit is an important but often misunderstood concept in Christian life.\n\n1. **Indwelling vs. filling**: Every believer receives the Spirit's indwelling at regeneration (Rom 8:9) — this is once-for-all and permanent. But Spirit-filling is an ongoing experience — Paul commands 'be filled with the Spirit' (Eph 5:18) using the present tense, indicating a continuous process.\n\n2. **What filling means**: Being filled with the Spirit isn't a mystical ecstatic experience, but the Spirit's complete control over one's thoughts, will, and emotions. Just as a drunk person is controlled by wine (Paul uses exactly this contrast in Eph 5:18), a Spirit-filled person is governed by the Spirit's influence.\n\n3. **Evidence of filling**: Spirit-filled people show several marks: praising God (Eph 5:19), giving thanks in everything (Eph 5:20), mutual submission (Eph 5:21), bearing the Spirit's fruit (Gal 5:22-23), and bold proclamation of truth (Acts 4:31).\n\n4. **How to be filled**: Spirit-filling isn't achieved by pursuing special experiences, but through confession, rooting in God's Word, persistent prayer, and faithful obedience. When we remove obstacles in our lives, the Spirit naturally fills us.\n\nCrucially: Spirit-filling isn't the privilege of a spiritual elite, but the normal state and responsibility of every believer.",
