    "id": "q084",
    "category": "uniqueness_of_jesus",
    "question_zh": "耶稣的复活有什么历史证据？",
    "question_en": "What is the historical evidence for Jesus' resurrection?",
    "short_answer_zh": "空坟墓、数百位目击证人、门徒从恐惧逃跑到甘愿殉道的巨变、以及教会在强烈逼迫下的爆发性增长——这些证据指向一个最合理的解释：耶稣确实复活了。",
    "short_answer_en": "The empty tomb, hundreds of eyewitnesses, the disciples' transformation from fearful fugitives to willing martyrs, and the church's explosive growth under persecution — all point to the most reasonable explanation: Jesus truly rose.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "耶稣的复活不仅是信仰宣告，也是经得起历史考验的事件。以下是几个关键的历史证据：\n\n1.【空坟墓】耶稣被埋葬在亚利马太的约瑟的新坟墓里，三天后坟墓是空的。连耶稣的敌人也不否认空坟墓，他们只是编造了门徒偷走尸体的谎言（太28:13）。但一群吓得四散奔逃的门徒怎么可能突破罗马士兵的守卫偷走尸体？\n\n2.【目击证人】保罗记载复活的基督「一时显给五百多弟兄看」（林前15:6），并说「其中一大半到如今还在」——这等于邀请读者去查证。这封信写于事件发生后约25年，还有大量证人在世。\n\n3.【门徒的转变】耶稣被捕时门徒四散逃跑，彼得三次不认主。但几周后，他们公开宣讲基督复活，甘愿为此受苦、殉道。人不会为自己明知是谎言的事去死。\n\n4.【女性证人】四卷福音书都记载最先发现空坟墓的是女性。在当时的文化中，女性的证词不被法庭采纳。如果是编造故事，绝不会选择女性作为第一证人——除非这确实是事实。\n\n5.【教会的诞生】基督教诞生于耶稣被处死的同一座城市。如果尸体还在，敌人只需展示尸体就能粉碎一切。但他们做不到。\n\n6.【雅各和保罗的转变】耶稣的弟弟雅各生前不信祂（约7:5），后来却成为耶路撒冷教会的领袖。逼迫基督徒的保罗成为最伟大的使徒。唯一合理的解释是他们真的遇见了复活的基督。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "Jesus' resurrection is not merely a faith claim but a historically testable event. Here are key lines of evidence:\n\n1. **The empty tomb**: Jesus was buried in Joseph of Arimathea's new tomb; three days later it was empty. Even Jesus' enemies didn't deny the empty tomb — they fabricated the story that disciples stole the body (Matt 28:13). But how could terrified, scattered disciples overpower Roman guards?\n\n2. **Eyewitnesses**: Paul records that the risen Christ 'appeared to more than five hundred brothers at one time' (1 Cor 15:6), adding 'most of whom are still alive' — essentially inviting readers to verify. This letter was written roughly 25 years after the event, with many witnesses still living.\n\n3. **Disciples' transformation**: At Jesus' arrest, the disciples fled; Peter denied Him three times. Yet weeks later, they publicly proclaimed Christ's resurrection, willingly suffering and dying for it. People don't die for what they know is a lie.\n\n4. **Female witnesses**: All four Gospels record women as the first to discover the empty tomb. In that culture, women's testimony was inadmissible in court. If inventing a story, no one would choose women as first witnesses — unless it was simply what happened.\n\n5. **The church's birth**: Christianity was born in the very city where Jesus was executed. If the body remained, enemies needed only to produce it. They couldn't.\n\n6. **James and Paul**: Jesus' brother James was a skeptic during His life (John 7:5) but became leader of the Jerusalem church. Paul, a persecutor of Christians, became the greatest apostle. The only reasonable explanation: they truly encountered the risen Christ.",
    "bible_verses": [
