    "id": "q085",
    "category": "uniqueness_of_jesus",
    "question_zh": "耶稣现在在做什么？",
    "question_en": "What is Jesus doing now?",
    "short_answer_zh": "耶稣升天后坐在父神的右边，掌管万有、为信徒代祷、借圣灵建造教会，并等待再来的时候。",
    "short_answer_en": "After ascending to heaven, Jesus sits at God's right hand, ruling over all things, interceding for believers, building His church through the Spirit, and awaiting the time of His return.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "许多人关注耶稣在地上的生平，却很少思考祂现在正在做什么。圣经告诉我们，复活升天的基督此刻正活跃地做着几件大事：\n\n1.【坐在父神的右边】「右边」在古代代表最高的权柄和尊荣（弗1:20-21）。耶稣坐下，表明祂在十字架上的救赎工作已经完成——不需要再次献祭。祂作为万王之王掌管宇宙万有。\n\n2.【为信徒代祷】希伯来书7:25说祂「长远活着，替他们祈求」。罗马书8:34说「基督……在神的右边，也替我们祈求。」想象一下：此时此刻，在天上，复活的基督正在为你祷告。这是信徒得蒙保守的终极保障。\n\n3.【借圣灵建造教会】耶稣升天后差遣圣灵（约16:7），借着圣灵继续祂在地上的工作——呼召罪人悔改、装备圣徒、赐下恩赐，使教会不断成长。\n\n4.【预备地方】耶稣说「我去原是为你们预备地方」（约14:2-3）。祂正在为每一位信徒预备永恒的居所。\n\n5.【等待再来】使徒行传3:21说天必留住基督，「等到万物复兴的时候」。祂将要再来，审判活人死人，建立新天新地。历史正在朝这个终点前进。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "Many focus on Jesus' earthly life but rarely consider what He's doing now. Scripture tells us the risen, ascended Christ is actively engaged in several things:\n\n1. **Seated at God's right hand**: 'Right hand' symbolized supreme authority and honor (Eph 1:20-21). Jesus' sitting down signifies His redemptive work on the cross is complete — no further sacrifice needed. He reigns as King of kings over all creation.\n\n2. **Interceding for believers**: Hebrews 7:25 says He 'always lives to make intercession for them.' Romans 8:34 says 'Christ Jesus... is at the right hand of God... interceding for us.' Right now, in heaven, the risen Christ is praying for you. This is the ultimate guarantee of believers' preservation.\n\n3. **Building His church through the Spirit**: After ascending, Jesus sent the Spirit (John 16:7), continuing His earthly work through Him — calling sinners to repentance, equipping saints, giving gifts, growing the church.\n\n4. **Preparing a place**: Jesus said, 'I go to prepare a place for you' (John 14:2-3). He's preparing an eternal dwelling for every believer.\n\n5. **Awaiting His return**: Acts 3:21 says heaven must receive Christ 'until the time for restoring all things.' He will return to judge the living and the dead and establish the new heaven and earth. History is moving toward this destination.",
    "bible_verses": [
