    "category": "church",
    "question_zh": "为什么要去教会？自己信不行吗？",
    "question_en": "Why go to church? Can't I just believe on my own?",
    "short_answer_zh": "基督徒的信仰不是个人独修，而是在基督身体中共同成长。教会是神设立的，提供敬拜、教导、团契、问责和互相服侍——这些是独自信主无法获得的。",
    "short_answer_en": "Christianity isn't solo spirituality but growing together in Christ's body. The church is God's design, providing worship, teaching, fellowship, accountability, and mutual service — things impossible to experience alone.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "「我自己读圣经祷告就行了，为什么要去教会？」这是一个很常见的想法，但它反映了对信仰本质的误解。\n\n1.【教会是神的设计】基督「爱教会，为教会舍己」（弗5:25）。教会不是人的发明，而是基督用自己的血买赎的群体。上帝拯救人不是让他们做独行侠，而是把他们加入一个新的家庭。\n\n2.【身体的比喻】保罗将教会比作基督的身体（林前12:12-27）。一只手不能对脚说「我不需要你」。每个信徒都是身体的一部分，彼此需要。离开教会的基督徒就像一块燃烧的煤从火堆中取出——很快就会熄灭。\n\n3.【教会提供什么】\n- 话语的教导：牧师蒙召忠心地传讲和教导圣经（提后4:2）\n- 圣礼：洗礼和圣餐是在教会中施行的\n- 团契和彼此相爱：新约有59条「彼此」的命令，无法在独处中完成\n- 属灵的问责：有人在你偏离时纠正你，在你软弱时扶持你\n- 使用恩赐的机会：你的恩赐是为了服侍别人而赐的\n\n4.【圣经的命令】希伯来书10:25直接命令「不可停止聚会，好像那些停止惯了的人」。这不是建议，而是命令。\n\n5.【教会不完美】是的，教会有很多问题——因为它是由罪人组成的。但上帝正是在这样不完美的群体中工作，磨炼、建造我们。逃避教会就是逃避上帝塑造你的一个重要方式。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "'I can read the Bible and pray by myself — why go to church?' This is common thinking, but it reflects a misunderstanding of faith's nature.\n\n1. **Church is God's design**: Christ 'loved the church and gave himself up for her' (Eph 5:25). The church isn't a human invention but a community Christ purchased with His blood. God saves people not as lone rangers but as members of a new family.\n\n2. **The body metaphor**: Paul compares the church to Christ's body (1 Cor 12:12-27). A hand can't say to the foot, 'I don't need you.' Every believer is part of the body, needing each other. A Christian apart from church is like a burning coal removed from the fire — it quickly goes cold.\n\n3. **What church provides**:\n- Biblical teaching: Pastors are called to faithfully preach and teach (2 Tim 4:2)\n- Sacraments: Baptism and the Lord's Supper are administered in community\n- Fellowship and mutual love: The NT contains 59 'one another' commands, impossible to fulfill alone\n- Spiritual accountability: Others correct you when you stray and support you when weak\n- Opportunity to use gifts: Your gifts were given to serve others\n\n4. **Biblical command**: Hebrews 10:25 directly commands 'not neglecting to meet together, as is the habit of some.' This isn't a suggestion but a command.\n\n5. **Church isn't perfect**: True — because it's made of sinners. But God works precisely in such imperfect community, refining and building us. Avoiding church means avoiding one of God's key instruments for shaping you.",
    "bible_verses": [
      "Ephesians 5:25",
      "1 Corinthians 12:12-27",
      "Hebrews 10:24-25",
