    "category": "existence_of_god",
    "question_zh": "人是按神的形象造的，这是什么意思？",
    "question_en": "What does it mean that humans are made in God's image?",
    "short_answer_zh": "按神的形象被造意味着人在所有受造物中独特地反映上帝的属性——理性、道德、关系、创造力和治理能力。这赋予每个人不可侵犯的尊严和价值。",
    "short_answer_en": "Being made in God's image means humans uniquely reflect God's attributes among all creatures — rationality, morality, relationality, creativity, and dominion. This gives every person inviolable dignity and worth.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "「神就照着自己的形象造人，乃是照着祂的形象造男造女」（创1:27）。这句话是人类尊严和价值的根基。\n\n1.【不是外在的相似】神的形象不是指人长得像上帝——上帝是灵（约4:24），没有物质身体。形象（imago Dei）指的是一种功能性和关系性的相似。\n\n2.【形象的内容】\n- 理性：人有思考、推理、认识真理的能力\n- 道德意识：人有是非之心，能分辨善恶\n- 关系性：上帝是三位一体的，本身就是关系；人也被造为关系性的存在——需要与上帝和他人建立关系\n- 创造力：人能创造艺术、音乐、文学、科技，反映造物主的创造性\n- 治理的使命：上帝赋予人管理大地的责任（创1:28），作为祂在地上的代表\n\n3.【罪的影响】堕落后，神的形象在人身上被严重扭曲但没有完全丧失。人仍然有理性和良知（创9:6仍以人有神的形象为不可杀人的理由），但这些能力被罪污染了。人不再完美地反映上帝，而是歪曲地反映。\n\n4.【在基督里恢复】歌罗西书3:10说信徒「穿上了新人，这新人……正如造他主的形象。」基督是「神本体的真像」（来1:3），成圣的过程就是我们越来越像基督——即恢复我们本应有的神的形象。\n\n5.【实际意义】每一个人——不论种族、能力、年龄、社会地位——都有按神形象而来的尊严。这是反对种族主义、歧视、堕胎、安乐死的最根本理由。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "'So God created man in his own image, in the image of God he created him; male and female he created them' (Gen 1:27). This statement is the foundation of human dignity and worth.\n\n1. **Not physical resemblance**: God's image doesn't mean humans look like God — God is spirit (John 4:24), without a physical body. Image (imago Dei) refers to functional and relational likeness.\n\n2. **Content of the image**:\n- Rationality: capacity for thought, reasoning, and knowing truth\n- Moral awareness: conscience, ability to distinguish good and evil\n- Relationality: God is Trinity, inherently relational; humans are also created as relational beings needing connection with God and others\n- Creativity: ability to create art, music, literature, technology, reflecting the Creator's creativity\n- Dominion mandate: God gave humans responsibility to steward the earth (Gen 1:28) as His representatives\n\n3. **Sin's effect**: After the Fall, God's image was severely distorted but not entirely lost. Humans still possess reason and conscience (Gen 9:6 still bases the prohibition of murder on the image of God), but these capacities are corrupted by sin. Humans no longer perfectly reflect God but do so in distorted ways.\n\n4. **Restored in Christ**: Colossians 3:10 says believers have 'put on the new self, which is being renewed... after the image of its creator.' Christ is 'the exact imprint of [God's] nature' (Heb 1:3), and sanctification is becoming increasingly Christlike — restoring the image we were meant to bear.\n\n5. **Practical implications**: Every person — regardless of race, ability, age, or social status — possesses dignity from God's image. This is the most fundamental argument against racism, discrimination, abortion, and euthanasia.",
    "bible_verses": [
      "Genesis 1:26-28",
      "Genesis 9:6",
      "John 4:24",
      "Colossians 3:10",
      "Hebrews 1:3",
      "James 3:9"
