    "question_zh": "信耶稣后，家中的偶像和神像该怎么处理？",
    "question_en": "After believing in Jesus, how should I handle the idols and images at home?",
    "short_answer_zh": "应当除去家中的偶像，因为基督徒只敬拜独一真神。处理时要温和智慧，尤其在家人尚未信主的情况下，可先沟通再行动。",
    "short_answer_en": "You should remove the idols from your home, since Christians worship only the one true God. Do so with wisdom and gentleness, especially if family members haven't yet believed — communicate first, then act.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "十诫的第一条和第二条明确禁止拜偶像（出埃及记20:3-5）。信主后除去偶像不是破坏文化，而是对真理的顺服。初代教会的信徒也是这样做的——以弗所的信徒「把行邪术的书拿来烧毁」（使徒行传19:19）。\n\n具体处理建议：\n\n1. **属于自己的偶像**：可以直接丢弃或销毁，不用担心所谓的「报应」，因为偶像本是虚无的（哥林多前书8:4），那些木头石头并没有真正的能力。\n\n2. **家人的偶像**：如果偶像属于尚未信主的家人，不宜强行丢弃。应先在爱中为家人祷告，用自己改变的生命来见证基督，等待合适的时机沟通。\n\n3. **内心态度**：最重要的不只是物理上除去偶像，更是心灵上弃绝对偶像的依赖和恐惧。有些人虽然扔掉了偶像，心里却仍然害怕——这说明需要更深地认识神的主权和保守。\n\n不要害怕。「那在你们里面的，比那在世界上的更大」（约翰一书4:4）。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "The first and second commandments clearly forbid idol worship (Exodus 20:3-5). Removing idols after conversion isn't cultural destruction but obedience to truth. The early church did likewise — believers in Ephesus 'brought their sorcery books and burned them publicly' (Acts 19:19).\n\nPractical suggestions:\n\n1. **Your own idols**: You can discard or destroy them directly. Don't fear 'retribution' — idols are nothing (1 Corinthians 8:4). Wood and stone have no real power.\n\n2. **Family members' idols**: If the idols belong to unbelieving family members, don't forcibly remove them. Pray for your family in love, witness through your transformed life, and wait for the right moment to communicate.\n\n3. **Heart attitude**: The most important thing isn't just physically removing idols but spiritually renouncing dependence on and fear of them. Some people discard idols yet remain afraid — this shows a need for deeper understanding of God's sovereignty and protection.\n\nDon't be afraid. 'He who is in you is greater than he who is in the world' (1 John 4:4).",
