    "id": "q108",
    "category": "sin_and_salvation",
    "question_zh": "「信耶稣得救」到底是什么意思？救什么？",
    "question_en": "What does 'believing in Jesus brings salvation' actually mean? Saved from what?",
    "short_answer_zh": "「得救」是从罪的刑罚、罪的权势和最终罪的存在中被拯救出来。信耶稣不只是来世去天堂，更是今生与神和好，获得新的生命。",
    "short_answer_en": "Salvation means being rescued from sin's penalty, sin's power, and ultimately sin's presence. Believing in Jesus isn't just about going to heaven — it's reconciliation with God and receiving new life now.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "很多人听到「得救」会困惑：我好好的，需要被救什么？这个问题其实触及了福音的核心。\n\n**得救包含三个层面：**\n\n1. **从罪的刑罚中得救（称义）**：人的罪使人与神隔绝，罪的工价是死（罗马书6:23）。耶稣替我们承受了这个刑罚，使信他的人不被定罪（罗马书8:1）。这是过去式——已经完成。\n\n2. **从罪的权势中得救（成圣）**：信主后，我们不再是罪的奴仆，而有了胜过罪的新能力（罗马书6:14）。圣灵在我们里面工作，使我们越来越像基督。这是进行式——持续一生。\n\n3. **从罪的存在中得救（得荣）**：将来基督再来时，我们会完全脱离罪恶和痛苦，得到复活的荣耀身体（腓立比书3:21）。这是将来式——盼望中等候。\n\n**得救也意味着：**\n- 与神和好：从敌人变为儿女（罗马书5:10）\n- 获得永生：不是将来才开始，而是从信的那一刻就拥有（约翰福音5:24）\n- 得到意义：人生不再是虚空，而是活在神的旨意中\n\n所以「信耶稣得救」不是一句宗教口号，而是涵盖过去、现在、将来的全面拯救。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "Many people are puzzled by 'salvation': I'm fine — saved from what? This question actually touches the heart of the gospel.\n\n**Salvation has three dimensions:**\n\n1. **Saved from sin's penalty (Justification)**: Human sin separates us from God; the wages of sin is death (Romans 6:23). Jesus bore this punishment for us, so that believers face no condemnation (Romans 8:1). This is past tense — already accomplished.\n\n2. **Saved from sin's power (Sanctification)**: After believing, we are no longer slaves to sin but have new power to overcome it (Romans 6:14). The Holy Spirit works within us, making us increasingly Christlike. This is present tense — ongoing throughout life.\n\n3. **Saved from sin's presence (Glorification)**: When Christ returns, we will be completely free from sin and suffering, receiving glorified resurrection bodies (Philippians 3:21). This is future tense — awaited in hope.\n\n**Salvation also means:**\n- Reconciliation with God: from enemies to children (Romans 5:10)\n- Eternal life: beginning not in the future but from the moment of faith (John 5:24)\n- Purpose: life is no longer meaningless but lived within God's will\n\n'Believing in Jesus brings salvation' is not a religious slogan but comprehensive rescue encompassing past, present, and future.",
    "bible_verses": [
      "Romans 6:23",
      "Romans 8:1",
      "Romans 6:14",
