    "id": "q114",
    "category": "eschatology",
    "question_zh": "信耶稣的人将来真的会复活吗？",
    "question_en": "Will believers in Jesus really be resurrected in the future?",
    "short_answer_zh": "是的。因为基督已经从死里复活，作了睡了之人初熟的果子。信他的人将来也必复活，得到不朽坏的荣耀身体。",
    "short_answer_en": "Yes. Because Christ has risen from the dead as the firstfruits of those who have fallen asleep, believers will also be raised and receive imperishable, glorified bodies.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "身体复活是基督教信仰的核心，不是可有可无的附加内容。保罗说：「若没有死人复活的事，基督也就没有复活。若基督没有复活，我们所传的便是枉然，你们所信的也是枉然」（哥林多前书15:13-14）。\n\n**复活的根基：基督已经复活。**\n耶稣的复活是历史事实，有空坟墓、数百位目击证人、门徒生命的彻底改变等多重证据。祂的复活不是灵魂不灭的象征，而是身体真实地从坟墓中出来。\n\n**信徒复活的应许：**\n「基督已经从死里复活，成为睡了之人初熟的果子」（哥林多前书15:20）。「初熟的果子」意味着后面还有收割——基督的复活保证了信徒的复活。\n\n**复活的身体是怎样的？**\n保罗在哥林多前书15章描述了：\n- 「所种的是必朽坏的，复活的是不朽坏的」（42节）\n- 「所种的是羞辱的，复活的是荣耀的」（43节）\n- 「所种的是软弱的，复活的是强壮的」（43节）\n\n复活的身体是真实的、物质的（就像耶稣复活后可以吃东西），但又是荣耀的、不朽的。这不是灵魂升天，而是身体被完全更新。\n\n基督教的盼望不是逃离物质世界，而是整个受造界——包括我们的身体——都将被救赎和更新（罗马书8:23）。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "Bodily resurrection is central to Christian faith — not an optional add-on. Paul says: 'If there is no resurrection of the dead, then not even Christ has been raised. And if Christ has not been raised, then our preaching is in vain and your faith is in vain' (1 Corinthians 15:13-14).\n\n**The foundation: Christ has already risen.**\nJesus' resurrection is historical fact, evidenced by the empty tomb, hundreds of eyewitnesses, and the apostles' radically transformed lives. His resurrection was not a symbol of the soul's immortality but a real body emerging from the grave.\n\n**The promise for believers:**\n'Christ has been raised from the dead, the firstfruits of those who have fallen asleep' (1 Corinthians 15:20). 'Firstfruits' implies a coming harvest — Christ's resurrection guarantees ours.\n\n**What will the resurrected body be like?**\nPaul describes it in 1 Corinthians 15:\n- 'What is sown is perishable; what is raised is imperishable' (v. 42)\n- 'It is sown in dishonor; it is raised in glory' (v. 43)\n- 'It is sown in weakness; it is raised in power' (v. 43)\n\nThe resurrection body is real and physical (like Jesus eating after His resurrection) yet glorious and imperishable. This isn't souls floating to heaven but bodies fully renewed.\n\nChristian hope isn't escape from the material world but the redemption and renewal of all creation — including our bodies (Romans 8:23).",
    "bible_verses": [
      "1 Corinthians 15:13-14",
      "1 Corinthians 15:20",
      "1 Corinthians 15:42-44",
