    "id": "q118",
    "category": "sin_and_salvation",
    "question_zh": "宗教会不会危害社会？信教是不是精神鸦片？",
    "question_en": "Doesn't religion harm society? Isn't it the 'opium of the people'?",
    "short_answer_zh": "马克思的「鸦片论」本身有特定历史背景，不能一概而论。真正的基督教信仰不是逃避现实，而是推动公义、仁慈和社会进步的强大力量。",
    "short_answer_en": "Marx's 'opium' critique had a specific historical context and shouldn't be generalized. Genuine Christian faith isn't escapism but a powerful force for justice, mercy, and social progress.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "「宗教是精神鸦片」是马克思的名言，但需要在完整的上下文和历史中来理解。\n\n**首先，澄清马克思的原意：**\n马克思的完整原话中，「鸦片」不完全是贬义——当时鸦片是穷人买得起的唯一止痛药。他是说宗教起到了安慰苦难者的作用，但这种安慰使人不去改变不公义的社会制度。\n\n**但这个批评对真正的基督教不成立：**\n\n1. **基督教是社会变革的推动力**：\n   - 早期基督徒改变了罗马帝国对婴儿遗弃、角斗表演的态度\n   - 威伯福斯因基督教信仰而推动废除奴隶贸易\n   - 马丁·路德·金的民权运动深深扎根于基督教信仰\n   - 现代医院、大学、慈善机构大量由基督徒建立\n\n2. **无神论政权的反面见证**：\n   20世纪废除宗教的政权（苏联、红色高棉、文化大革命）造成了人类历史上最大规模的迫害和苦难。事实证明，消灭宗教不仅没有解放人类，反而带来了更大的压迫。\n\n3. **圣经的社会关怀**：\n   「世人哪，耶和华已指示你何为善，他向你所要的是什么呢？只要你行公义，好怜悯，存谦卑的心，与你的神同行」（弥迦书6:8）。真正的信仰不是逃避，而是积极参与、改变世界。\n\n基督教信仰给人尊严（人是按照神的形象造的）、给社会伦理基础（客观的道德标准）、给受苦者盼望（不是虚假的安慰，而是永恒的应许）。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "The quote 'religion is the opium of the people' is from Marx, but it must be understood in its full context.\n\n**First, clarifying Marx's original meaning:**\nIn Marx's full text, 'opium' wasn't entirely pejorative — opium was the only affordable painkiller for the poor at the time. He meant religion comforted the suffering, but this comfort prevented people from changing unjust social systems.\n\n**But this critique doesn't hold for genuine Christianity:**\n\n1. **Christianity has driven social transformation:**\n   - Early Christians changed Roman attitudes toward infant abandonment and gladiatorial games\n   - Wilberforce pushed to abolish the slave trade because of his Christian faith\n   - Martin Luther King Jr.'s civil rights movement was deeply rooted in Christianity\n   - Modern hospitals, universities, and charities were largely built by Christians\n\n2. **The counter-witness of atheistic regimes:**\n   20th-century regimes that abolished religion (Soviet Union, Khmer Rouge, Cultural Revolution) produced the largest-scale persecution and suffering in human history. Eliminating religion didn't liberate humanity but brought greater oppression.\n\n3. **The Bible's social concern:**\n   'He has told you, O man, what is good; and what does the Lord require of you but to do justice, love kindness, and walk humbly with your God' (Micah 6:8). True faith isn't escape but active engagement in transforming the world.\n\nChristian faith gives individuals dignity (humans made in God's image), gives society an ethical foundation (objective moral standards), and gives the suffering hope (not false comfort but eternal promise).",
    "bible_verses": [
