    "id": "q120",
    "category": "sin_and_salvation",
    "question_zh": "我犯的罪太多太大了，神还会接纳我吗？",
    "question_en": "I've committed too many and too terrible sins. Will God still accept me?",
    "short_answer_zh": "会的！圣经说「基督耶稣降世为要拯救罪人，这话是可信的，是十分可佩服的；在罪人中我是个罪魁」。没有任何罪大到基督的宝血不能赦免。",
    "short_answer_en": "Yes! The Bible says 'Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners, of whom I am the foremost.' No sin is too great for Christ's blood to forgive.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "这种感受说明你的良心是活的，你对罪的严重性有所认识——这是好事。但你需要知道一个更大的事实：神的恩典远远超过你的罪。\n\n**圣经中的伟大罪人如何被接纳：**\n\n- **大卫**：犯了奸淫和谋杀，但悔改后被称为「合神心意的人」\n- **保罗**：迫害基督徒、参与杀害司提反，却成为最伟大的使徒，自称「罪人中的罪魁」（提摩太前书1:15）\n- **十字架上的强盗**：一生犯罪，临死前信了耶稣，当天就与主同在乐园（路加福音23:43）\n- **彼得**：三次否认主，却被恢复并成为教会的柱石\n\n**神恩典的大小：**\n「罪在哪里显多，恩典就更显多了」（罗马书5:20）。不管你的罪有多大，基督在十字架上的牺牲完全足够覆盖。祂不是为小罪而死——祂为全人类一切的罪而死。\n\n**真正的危险不是罪太大：**\n真正的危险是骄傲地拒绝恩典。法利赛人以为自己够好，不需要救主——他们离神比那些「大罪人」更远。觉得自己罪太大不配得救，听起来谦卑，其实是低估了基督宝血的功效。\n\n来吧，就像你现在的样子来到神面前。「凡劳苦担重担的人，可以到我这里来，我就使你们得安息」（马太福音11:28）。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "This feeling shows your conscience is alive and you recognize the seriousness of sin — that's good. But you need to know a greater truth: God's grace far exceeds your sin.\n\n**Great sinners in the Bible who were accepted:**\n\n- **David**: Committed adultery and murder, yet after repentance was called 'a man after God's own heart'\n- **Paul**: Persecuted Christians and participated in Stephen's killing, yet became the greatest apostle, calling himself 'the foremost of sinners' (1 Timothy 1:15)\n- **The thief on the cross**: A lifetime criminal who believed in Jesus at the point of death and was immediately promised paradise (Luke 23:43)\n- **Peter**: Denied Jesus three times, yet was restored and became a pillar of the church\n\n**The magnitude of God's grace:**\n'Where sin increased, grace abounded all the more' (Romans 5:20). No matter how great your sin, Christ's sacrifice on the cross is more than sufficient to cover it. He didn't die for small sins — He died for all the sins of all humanity.\n\n**The real danger isn't having too much sin:**\nThe real danger is proudly refusing grace. The Pharisees thought they were good enough and didn't need a Savior — they were further from God than the 'great sinners.' Feeling too sinful to be saved sounds humble but actually underestimates the power of Christ's blood.\n\nCome as you are. 'Come to me, all who labor and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest' (Matthew 11:28).",
