    "id": "q123",
    "category": "sin_and_salvation",
    "question_zh": "某些基督徒的行为很差，让我不想信。",
    "question_en": "Some Christians behave terribly, which puts me off believing.",
    "short_answer_zh": "基督徒的失败恰恰证明了福音的核心信息：人人都是需要恩典的罪人。你信的是完美的基督，不是不完美的基督徒。",
    "short_answer_en": "Christians' failures actually prove the gospel's core message: everyone is a sinner in need of grace. You place your faith in the perfect Christ, not in imperfect Christians.",
    "detailed_answer_zh": "你的失望完全可以理解。看到自称基督徒的人行为虚伪、自私甚至邪恶，确实令人反感。但请考虑以下几点：\n\n**1. 基督教从未宣称基督徒是完美的。**\n恰恰相反，基督教的出发点就是「所有人都是罪人」（罗马书3:23）。教会不是完人的俱乐部，而是罪人的医院。如果基督徒个个完美无缺，那反而证明福音是不需要的。\n\n**2. 区分基督和基督徒。**\n判断一套医学理论好不好，应该看这个理论本身，而不是看某个不称职的医生。同样，判断基督教的真伪，应该看耶稣基督本人——祂的教导、祂的生命、祂的牺牲——而不是某些不合格的跟随者。\n\n**3. 不要让别人的罪阻碍你的救恩。**\n在最后的审判中，你不会因为别人的行为被审判，只会为自己的选择交账。因为张三是坏基督徒就拒绝基督，就像因为某个医生态度差就拒绝救命的药——受害的是你自己。\n\n**4. 也看看信仰的好果子。**\n历史上和你身边，一定也有生命被基督改变、活出美好见证的基督徒。不要只看最差的，也看看最好的——更重要的是，看基督本身。\n\n**5. 虚伪的基督徒恰恰是耶稣最严厉谴责的。**\n耶稣对法利赛人的批评比对任何人都严厉（马太福音23章）。所以你对虚伪行为的反感，其实和耶稣站在同一边。",
    "detailed_answer_en": "Your disappointment is completely understandable. Seeing self-proclaimed Christians act hypocritically, selfishly, or even wickedly is genuinely repulsive. But consider these points:\n\n**1. Christianity never claims Christians are perfect.**\nQuite the opposite — Christianity's starting point is 'all have sinned' (Romans 3:23). The church isn't a club for saints but a hospital for sinners. If Christians were all flawless, it would prove the gospel unnecessary.\n\n**2. Distinguish between Christ and Christians.**\nYou judge a medical theory by the theory itself, not by an incompetent doctor. Similarly, judge Christianity by Jesus Christ Himself — His teaching, His life, His sacrifice — not by some unqualified followers.\n\n**3. Don't let others' sin block your salvation.**\nAt the final judgment, you won't be judged for others' behavior — only your own choices. Rejecting Christ because of a bad Christian is like refusing life-saving medicine because of a rude doctor — you're the one who suffers.\n\n**4. Also see faith's good fruit.**\nThroughout history and around you, there are certainly Christians whose lives have been beautifully transformed by Christ. Don't look only at the worst — look also at the best, and most importantly, look at Christ Himself.\n\n**5. Hypocritical Christians are precisely whom Jesus most harshly condemned.**\nJesus' criticism of the Pharisees was fiercer than toward anyone else (Matthew 23). Your disgust at hypocrisy actually puts you on the same side as Jesus.",
